cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY 

The paper discusses improving sample efficiency in model-free reinforcement learning from images, which involves topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper specifically focuses on learning good latent features for image-based RL, which is a common problem in machine learning and AI research. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses using image reconstruction loss, which is a common technique in computer vision research (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper applies the proposed algorithm to control tasks, which falls under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
